  "texts": [
    "One is the mass-sheet degeneracy or mass-sheet transformation (or MST), because its limiting case (multiplying the lens equation by zero) makes (θ) = cr everywhere.",
    "Another name is the steepness degeneracy, since making the mass distribution less or more like a uniform sheet makes the mass profile steeper or shallower.",
    "Yet another name is the magnification transformation, because rescaling β with θ fixed implies changing the magnification.",
    "As expected from the wavefront picture, having more lensed sources reduces the effect of lensing degeneracies.",
    "Having more images reduces the scope of the monopole degeneracy, because there is less area available to redistribute mass."
  ],
